  "text": "Wnt5 mutants were shown to exhibit a similar type of ␣/␤ lobe defects as the core PCP mutants [CITATION_1] Shimizu et al., 2011) , and Wnt5 genetically interacts with fz, dsh and Vang (Shimizu et al., 2011) , indicating that Wnt5 may function as a ligand for the PCP pathway during MB development. Supporting this possibility, we found that Wnt5 400 is a strong enhancer of dDAAM Ex1 with respect to the MB axonal growth phenotypes (Fig. 5D) . These results suggest that the Wnt5/PCP pathway governs actin dynamics in the growth cone by activating dDAAM, a formin directly involved in actin regulation, and supports the notion that Wnt5 acts as a PCP ligand in the MB neurons.",
