      "span_text": "Wnt5 mutants were shown to exhibit a similar type of ␣/␤ lobe defects as the core PCP mutants [CITATION_1] Shimizu et al., 2011) , and Wnt5 genetically interacts with fz, dsh and Vang (Shimizu et al., 2011) , indicating that Wnt5 may function as a ligand for the PCP pathway during MB development.",
